NIT - Ultra-Tight Passive Player

PROFILE:
- VPIP: 10-14%
- PFR: 8-12%
- 3-bet: 3-4% (only premiums)
- Only plays premium hands
- Folds to any aggression without the nuts
- Easy to bluff but hard to get value from
- When they bet, they have it

OPEN RAISE (2.5bb) - Very selective

UTG (9%):
TT+, AQs+, AKo

MP (11%):
99+, AJs+, KQs, AQo+

CO (14%):
88+, ATs+, KQs, AJo+, KQo

BTN (18%):
77+, A9s+, KJs+, QJs, ATo+, KJo+

SB (15%):
88+, ATs+, KQs, AJo+

VS SINGLE OPEN - Tight and straightforward

3-bet value:
QQ+, AKs, AKo

3-bet bluff:
(none - nits don't bluff)

Call (tight):
JJ-99, AQs, AJs, KQs

BB DEFENSE (folds too much)

vs BTN:
- 3-bet: QQ+, AKs, AKo
- Call: JJ-77, AQs-ATs, KQs-KJs, QJs
- Fold: everything else

vs CO/MP/UTG:
- 3-bet: QQ+, AKs, AKo
- Call: JJ-88, AQs-AJs, KQs
- Fold: everything else

VS 3-BET (folds too much)

4-bet: KK+
Call: QQ, AKs
Fold: JJ, TT, AKo, AQs, everything else

VS 4-BET

All-in: AA
Fold: everything including KK sometimes

POSTFLOP TENDENCIES:
- Only continues with top pair+
- Folds to any aggression without strong hand
- Never bluffs
- Easy to push off medium hands
- When they raise, they have the nuts
